    <section id="body">
        <h2>Understanding Quantum Reflection & Superposition</h2>
        <p>Quantum Reflection refers to the phenomenon where particles reflect off a potential barrier rather than passing through it, even without direct contact. Superposition allows quantum states to exist in multiple configurations until observed. These properties enable:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Breakthroughs in quantum computing</li>
            <li>New insights into fundamental physics</li>
            <li>Innovative applications in secure communication</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h3>Key Applications</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Quantum Computing:</strong> Superposition allows qubits to hold multiple values at once, vastly increasing computational power.</li>
            <li><strong>Quantum Encryption:</strong> Secure information transmission leveraging superposition and entanglement.</li>
            <li><strong>Advanced Material Science:</strong> Understanding wave-particle duality aids in designing novel materials.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
    
